e sense that shareholders get used to dividends and get mad if they are cut=
, while a buyback program can increase and decrease in size without locking=
 the company in much.</p>
</div>
<div id=3D"footnote-14" class=3D"footnote-content" style=3D"font-style: ita=
lic;">
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">[14] I mean there=E2=80=99s apparently some im=
precise rounding there but never mind.</p>
</div>
<div id=3D"footnote-15" class=3D"footnote-content" style=3D"font-style: ita=
lic;">
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">[15] Of course the $1.6 billion number doesn=
=E2=80=99t count the taxes on capital gains from sales into the $169 billio=
n of buybacks, but presumably that number is a lot lower than $33.8 billion=
 too.</p>
</div>
